=== Pain Management
<subsec:ped-severe-pain>

Pain is common in pediatric ME/CFS, including widespread musculoskeletal pain, headaches, and abdominal pain. Pain management in developing nervous systems requires particular caution.

==== Non-Pharmacological Approaches

Non-pharmacological strategies should be first-line:

    - *Positioning*: Supportive pillows, position changes to relieve pressure
    - *Heat/cold*: Heating pads for muscle pain; cold packs for acute inflammation or headaches
    - *Gentle massage*: Light massage by caregiver (not deep tissue; avoid triggering PEM)
    - *TENS units*: Transcutaneous electrical nerve stimulation for localized pain
    - *Distraction*: Audio content (audiobooks, music, podcasts) at tolerable volumes

